verification_checks:
  - "A local server is the source of truth even with one connected user."
  - "Join form allows generated/overridden name and color plus paid/free toggle."
  - "web-canvas/assets/back.png and web-canvas/assets/start.png exist and are the runtime paths used by render.js/style.css."
  - "After joining, the CSS background layer repeats back.png beneath the transparent gameplay canvas and shifts weakly on both axes as the followed fish moves."
  - "Crossing a wrapped world edge does not make the CSS background tile jump; the accumulated parallax phase remains visually continuous across the edge."
  - "The CSS in-game background haze is lighter at the top and darker at the bottom."
  - "When the join panel is visible, start.png is visible as the entry background while the join form remains readable."
  - "Each client controls only its own user fish."
  - "After automatic reconnect, pressing or exposing the join flow cannot create a second ownerKind='user' fish for the same client instance or temporaryConnectionCode."
  - "Unexpected socket break has a 3 second reconnect grace, then fish becomes NPC."
  - "Explicit leave immediately converts to NPC unless active user-vs-user attack window blocks it."
  - "After a successful explicit leave, the HUD command changes from Выйти to Войти; pressing Войти opens the start join form with name, color, and paid/free controls for creating a new user fish."
  - "Server broadcasts world events and coordinate corrections; client prediction cannot override server events."
  - "World edges wrap horizontally and vertically without stopping fish."
  - "World resize scales fish coordinates but not fish sizes; clients animate resize playback."
  - "NPC count follows target density over world area."
  - "NPC spawn and user respawn choose areas with lowest current density over all fish."
  - "New NPC spawn positions are free water candidates that account for current fish positions, sizes, density, and attack zones before falling back to the least risky candidate."
  - "New NPC fish appear as fry and grow to nominal start size over 10 seconds."
  - "New NPC fish receive courage from the live-NPC average plus bounded jitter, with every tenth spawn fully random."
  - "NPC threat assessment considers all fish that can potentially eat the NPC by size/type, independent of current movement mode."
  - "Hunting NPCs may correct their vector by at most 20 degrees from the victim direction to reduce predator danger."
  - "Fleeing NPCs sample the full circle and choose the lowest summed danger direction using fish radii and attack zones."
  - "NPC direction and acceleration choices change smoothly through configurable decision inertia tunables."
  - "NPC fish have an active wander, hunt, or flee motion intent on every server tick, aside from brief physical transitions caused by inertia."
  - "NPC fish reaching 5 minutes of age disappear by old-age death, not predation, and no predator receives eaten credit."
  - "Old-age NPC death creates edible drifting shreds with total geometric area equal to the configured ratio of the dead NPC canonical circular area."
  - "Fish can eat shreds in burst or cruise when contact, size threshold, and minimum feeding speed are satisfied."
  - "A fish with feedingCooldown > 0 performs no feeding attempts, while feedingSuccessFactor continues restoring toward 1."
  - "When a fish contacts multiple edible fish/shreds, the server sorts candidates by expected nutrition and processes one feeding batch."
  - "Each attempted candidate uses the current feedingSuccessFactor probability, applies the food-type decay factor after the attempt, and starts a 0.35s cooldown after the series."
  - "A batch cannot successfully swallow more canonical area than the feeder fish's own canonical area."
  - "A batch whose first candidate is a shred starts with success probability capped at 0.4."
  - "Each shred is consumed layer-by-layer, applies x3 nutrition mass, and does not increment eatenFishCount."
  - "The first two 30% shred layers apply same-color or HSV-similarity nutrition factors; remaining layers feed all fish uniformly."
  - "Shreds are synchronized to clients and rendered from the published web-canvas/assets/shred.svg runtime copy of canonical ds/assets/shred.svg with client-only layer drift."
  - "Paid user fish can be eaten only by paid user fish; free user fish can be eaten by any ordinary eligible predator."
  - "The UI has no separate user-fish vulnerability toggle; eligibility comes from paid/free tier."
  - "Abandoned former user fish loses user-tier protection and uses former color to NPC-yellow gradient."
  - "Abandoned former user fish applies that gradient only to the body base; fins, eyes, mouth, highlights, and other SVG layers keep their normal authored treatment."
  - "Predation requires attack contact: burst predator, size/type eligibility, victim in the head/mouth area, and relative motion increasing canonical circle overlap."
  - "A burst attack that reaches an eligible smaller fish through the mouth/head area triggers eating without requiring pixel-perfect center overlap."
  - "Remote fish motion is rendered smoothly between authoritative snapshots."
  - "Remote fish crossing a world edge interpolates through the nearest toroidal path instead of flashing across the center of the map."
  - "When the followed fish is near a wrapped edge, NPC fish near the opposite canonical edge are drawn at the nearest toroidal image relative to the followed fish, for example x=10 as x=110 when the followed fish is at x=90 in width=100."
  - "Decorative bubbles are generated, advanced, and rendered client-side from visible fish state."
  - "Removed fish disappear on clients immediately after an e tombstone delta row."
  - "Keyboard key-down/key-up and burst transitions are sent without waiting for the idle input cadence."
  - "Space enables burst in keyboard, pointer, touch, and joystick modes."
  - "The initial screen control mode is visual joystick/default on every device; keyboard input is always active."
  - "The game surface and game controls suppress browser selection, scrolling, zooming, context gestures, and navigation gestures while the join form remains normally editable."
  - "The game menu shows a persistent version string derived from launch/build date and commit digest."
  - "The top-left menu contains control mode selection, version, debug activation, leave command, and help text for the active control mode."
  - "In joystick mode, the steering joystick is on the right side of the screen and radial distance selects cruise or burst target speed 1..99."
  - "Losing focus clears local key and pointer/touch pressed state so movement and burst cannot remain stuck."
  - "Unchanged input sends p:${N} at one-second cadence, with no faster ping heartbeat."
  - "User fish body decoration preserves the selected user color across the full body through transparent overlays."
  - "Fish rendering uses the published web-canvas/assets/fish2.svg runtime copy of canonical ds/assets/fish2.svg semantic ids for canonical collision_area, cruise/burst shape groups, and animated fin_* parts."
  - "An open mouth uses the legacy curved snout cavity and small predator teeth."
  - "Only the current client's own user fish shows green +0.1-step size gain labels and red -0.1-step size loss labels; continuous losses accumulate discretely and labels fade while rising."
  - "User respawn preserves paid/free type."
  - "The WebSocket protocol uses ASCII string messages, base64url names, delta controls, handshake setup, shared absolute/delta world sync, compact fish rows, state mods, and specific client events."
  - "Camera follows the current client's user fish."
  - "serializeFish includes user name/color/tier only for user fish."
  - "Debug mode can be toggled locally and has no server/protocol side effect."
  - "Debug mode draws the repeating world rectangle at the current world min/max bounds."
  - "Debug position traces show client-computed points in yellow and absolute server points in green; each point stays visible for 3 seconds and then fades out."
  - "Fish visual facing is derived from movement, while toothed chase mouth opens only for burst/hunt, not ordinary steering or cruise movement."
  - "Remote fish tail/fin animation continues during server-authoritative rendering at cruise speed and during burst."
  - "A large user fish in hunt/burst can reach at least FISH.minBurstSpeed, which is greater than PREY.maxSpeed + PREY.speedMargin, while ordinary NPC prey remains capped by PREY.maxSpeed even during flee acceleration."
  - "A user fish depleted by burst remains larger than PREY.minSize by the predation margin and can still eat the smallest fully grown ordinary NPC."

preferred_agent: "strong coding model for IMP; server/client split is non-trivial"
